An awesome map for any number of players, a hidden gun bonus on each side of the map to make it a bit fair, shoot through the middle wall to get to the enemies side faster but watch out because there may be a camper watching you from one of the 2 towers on each side, the towers are spacious enough to have a bunch of people in them and then they also have a balcony/bridge thing with a glass shield that will take some of the damage away from the shots being fired at you if that is what you need. 2 pools (mainly for aesthetic reasons =D) that you can jump into from the tower bridges so you dont get hurt.

even if you disable weapons and just want to have a knife fight, this map will be a great choice


happy gaming and happy new year!
 , copenicaz

This is my first official beta for cs_little_forest. With this being the first beta I need to know what I can do to improve this map. There is a lot of work to be done on this, but I need to know what you guys think since you will be the ones playing on the map. :] So far the map features: -Lots of ambient sounds -Lots of cover -Foliage -Buy zones for each side -Lake with fish -Steam coming from the water -The world is cold so players will see each others breath -Wind Still adding: -More to the design/layout -HDR (when I have the map 100% complete) -Optimization -More displacements -More lakes and paths -Looking to add cliffs This takes place in an early morning battle, birds will chirps, frogs will croak, steam rises from the water. Players will see each other breath, after all it is fall and it's cold. :] I'm hoping the map gives some environmental vibes off to the players. Please keep in mind this is my first beta, so this in not the final product! Any suggestions, feedback, or ideas are welcome, but please don't rate this map a 4 then give no reason. I need your feed back to improve this map to a proper release! I thank you all for taking a look at my map, and those of you who take the time to help me out with it give feed back and ideas. Enjoy b1, and look for my full release to come out soon, I hope. -tpskjarhead

First of all, this is my first map submission, and was the product of my first time using Hammer. Second, I couldn't find any way to contact the original author, so I don't have any permission or anything, but since I'm posting the original readme, and give credit where credit is due, I think this is not a problem? Original readme stated: --------------------------------------------------------
Map: cs_bloodstrike Type: deathmatch Author: Stinger Email: zithri@hotmail.com Description: This is a remake of the classic Counter-Strike map, cs_bloodstrike. This version includes barrels, fog and cool lighting. Early on, I saw the cs_bloodstrike_s map, but it looked like it had been put together in five seconds, with textures done poorly and all sorts. So I decided to try and do a better version of it. I hope you like it. Also included is a nav file for the bots. Installation: Place the cs_bloodstrike.bsp, cs_bloodstrike.txt and cs_bloodstrike.nav into your ...\Steam\SteamApps\username\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps folder. And have fun!
-------------------------------------------------------- I'm someone that likes a bit of eye candy along with the gameplay, so I got bored pretty fast with the bland textures in the original. I decided to edit them, which was my first time using Hammer. I added a couple of props, decals, and some amateur brushwork. And of course the overall texture change. I liked the result, and think it's better to look at while not ruining the gameplay in any way. Had doubts about submitting it without permission or anything, so if I'm breaking any written or unwritten rule here, please tell me :). Compare to original here: http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/4409 NOTE: I did NOT create this map or it's layout. It's an edit of an existing map! I am merely posting this for others to enjoy, not to take any credit!
